{\an8}<i>♪ Do I look good,</i>
<i>my dear? ♪</i>

00:13.221 --> 00:15.932
{\an8}<i>♪ Do I look good today? ♪</i>

00:16.015 --> 00:18.143
{\an8}<i>♪ Today, today ♪</i>

00:18.226 --> 00:20.061
{\an8}<i>♪ Ooh ooh ooh ♪</i>

00:21.521 --> 00:24.524
{\an8}<i>♪ I'm just another</i>
<i>kind of girl ♪</i>

00:25.859 --> 00:29.404
{\an8}<i>♪ And you want</i>
<i>to see my world ♪</i>

00:29.487 --> 00:32.281
{\an8}<i>♪ So come and run away ♪</i>

00:32.365 --> 00:34.409
{\an8}<i>♪ Yeah, yeah ♪</i>

00:34.492 --> 00:36.619
{\an8}<i>♪ If you wanna play ♪</i>

00:36.703 --> 00:38.621
{\an8}<i>♪ Come and play today ♪</i>

00:38.705 --> 00:42.584
{\an8}<i>♪ Let's just get away, yeah ♪</i>

00:42.667 --> 00:45.295
{\an8}<i>♪ I will make you see ♪</i>

00:45.378 --> 00:47.005
{\an8}<i>♪ All of the things ♪</i>

00:47.088 --> 00:49.132
{\an8}<i>♪ That you can be ♪</i>

00:49.215 --> 00:51.134
{\an8}<i>♪ Believe in yourself ♪</i>

00:51.217 --> 00:54.220
{\an8}<i>♪ Come follow me ♪</i>

00:54.304 --> 00:56.473
{\an8}<i>♪ Yeah, yeah ♪</i>

00:56.556 --> 00:57.265
{\an8}<i>♪ Yeah ♪</i>

01:02.228 --> 01:05.147
{\an8}<i>[laid-back music]</i>

01:05.230 --> 01:06.441
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:06.524 --> 01:10.987
{\an8}MR. BERRINGER: And so
gravitational potential energy

01:11.070 --> 01:13.823
{\an8}is proportional
to height and mass.

01:13.907 --> 01:15.408
{\an8}For example,

01:15.492 --> 01:17.452
{\an8}raising two similar objects

01:17.535 --> 01:19.913
{\an8}or the same object twice as far

01:19.996 --> 01:24.125
{\an8}doubles the potential energy

01:24.209 --> 01:26.085
{\an8}as expressed by...

01:28.421 --> 01:31.591
{\an8}Why do I feel like Quinn
is the only one who cares?

01:31.674 --> 01:33.343
- Even I don't care.

01:33.426 --> 01:34.511
MR. BERRINGER: Oh.

01:34.594 --> 01:36.513
I'm a boring teacher.

01:36.596 --> 01:40.350
- No.
- Not at all.

01:40.433 --> 01:42.143
- Yeah, you aren't boring.

01:42.227 --> 01:44.646
- I knew, I shouldn't have been
a physics teacher.

01:44.729 --> 01:46.815
I wanted to work at the zoo.

01:46.898 --> 01:48.233
- When's lunch?

01:48.316 --> 01:49.984
- It's 8:30 in the morning.

01:50.068 --> 01:52.529
- Look, we wouldn't be so bored
if you could relate physics

01:52.612 --> 01:54.364
to something that isn't so--

01:54.447 --> 01:55.698
you know?

01:55.782 --> 01:57.534
Insanely boring.

01:57.617 --> 01:59.410
- Right...

01:59.494 --> 02:02.330
like a water-driven turbine

02:02.413 --> 02:04.874
or a Tesla coil, hmm.

02:04.958 --> 02:07.961
[all murmuring]

02:11.506 --> 02:14.342
What is a roller toaster?
- Coaster.

02:14.425 --> 02:16.219
Oh, oh, right, right.

02:16.302 --> 02:17.846
Roller coasters.

02:17.929 --> 02:20.014
MR. BERRINGER:
Yes, yes, roller coasters

02:20.098 --> 02:22.934
are all about the principles
of physics.

02:23.017 --> 02:25.770
You see, when the cars
are at top of a tall hill,

02:25.854 --> 02:28.398
they have potential energy.

02:28.481 --> 02:30.567
- Mr. Berringer, if I may?

02:30.650 --> 02:32.902
Instead of talking
about roller coasters,

02:32.986 --> 02:34.654
don't you feel we can learn more
about physics

02:34.737 --> 02:36.364
by actually riding one?

02:36.447 --> 02:38.324
- Yes.
- Keep talking handsome.

02:38.408 --> 02:39.951
JAMES: In the spirit of physics,

02:40.034 --> 02:41.202
I suggest this entire class

02:41.286 --> 02:43.162
take a field trip
to Mystic Mountain.

02:43.246 --> 02:44.372
- Yeah.

02:44.455 --> 02:46.291
- Well, I--I'm not sure
if we should--

02:46.374 --> 02:48.084
- Yes, you are.
- But I--

02:48.167 --> 02:49.294
- Awesome.

02:49.377 --> 02:50.628
- We're all going
on a roller coaster.

02:50.712 --> 02:52.839
- Okay!

02:52.922 --> 02:55.967
[all cheering]

02:57.677 --> 03:05.727
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:05.810 --> 03:07.478
- What's up?
- Hey.

03:15.862 --> 03:17.322
- Didn't I have a hamburger?

03:17.405 --> 03:19.032
- I'm having fruit.

03:20.658 --> 03:22.035
- Hey.
LOGAN: What's up?

03:22.118 --> 03:23.161
LOGAN: Hi, guys.

03:23.244 --> 03:24.287
- You guys see
a hamburger anywhere?

03:24.370 --> 03:25.705
- No.
- I don't think so.

03:25.788 --> 03:26.789
LOGAN: It's so weird.

03:26.873 --> 03:30.001
I went through the lunch line,

03:30.084 --> 03:31.628
I put a hamburger on my tray.

03:31.711 --> 03:35.131
- Found ya.
- Hey, lil' Lisa.

03:35.214 --> 03:38.301
- Hey, I heard our yoga class
this afternoon was cancelled.

03:38.384 --> 03:40.887
- Yeah, Ms. Dangle
rode her bike into a tree.

03:40.970 --> 03:42.972
- Isn't that, like,
the third time she's done that?

03:44.891 --> 03:45.975
- Anybody lose a hamburger?

03:46.059 --> 03:47.435
I found this in the fountain.

03:47.518 --> 03:49.646
- Yeah, I think that's mine.

04:00.406 --> 04:03.117
- Michael,
can I borrow your knife?

04:03.201 --> 04:05.286
Michael?

04:05.370 --> 04:06.579
- Michael.

04:06.663 --> 04:07.789
- Yeah, yeah.
[chuckles]

04:07.872 --> 04:10.166
I love you too, baby.

04:10.249 --> 04:12.043
- I asked if I could borrow
your knife.

04:12.126 --> 04:13.378
- Yeah, I heard you.

04:13.461 --> 04:15.672
- So how was physics?
ZOEY: Good.

04:15.755 --> 04:17.339
We're gonna take a field trip
to Mystic Mountain

04:17.423 --> 04:18.925
and ride a roller coaster
so we can study kinetic--

04:19.007 --> 04:22.178
- Can we stop talking
about roller coasters already?

04:22.262 --> 04:23.554
- That was the first time I--

04:23.638 --> 04:25.515
- I don't know
why we can't just eat lunch

04:25.598 --> 04:26.933
without me hearing
roller coasters,

04:27.016 --> 04:29.852
roller coasters, roller
coasters, roller coasters.

04:29.936 --> 04:31.062
I don't remember signing up

04:31.145 --> 04:32.772
for the roller coaster
lunch club.

04:32.855 --> 04:34.190
- Michael, what's wrong?

04:34.274 --> 04:35.483
- Nothing. Good-bye.

04:37.276 --> 04:38.695
- What was that about?

04:38.778 --> 04:40.446
- You're his girlfriend,
you tell us.

04:40.530 --> 04:43.908
- Maybe he's--
- I'm afraid.

04:43.992 --> 04:45.535
I'm afraid of roller coasters.

04:45.618 --> 04:47.745
I have been
ever since I was little.

04:47.829 --> 04:50.039
I don't wanna go
to Mystic Mountain.

04:50.123 --> 04:51.833
- Oh, Michael.

04:51.916 --> 04:53.084
- There's nothing
to be afraid of.

04:53.167 --> 04:54.877
- Roller coasters
are totally safe.

04:54.961 --> 04:56.713
- What a nub.
- You see?

04:56.796 --> 04:58.881
I knew he'd do that.
I knew he'd make fun of me.

04:58.965 --> 05:01.551
- Stop it.
- Yeah.

05:01.634 --> 05:02.719
- And if you tell anyone else--

05:02.802 --> 05:04.220
- He won't.
LOGAN: Yeah.

05:04.303 --> 05:05.680
Why would I want people to know

05:05.763 --> 05:07.807
my roommate's basically
a three-year-old girl?

05:07.890 --> 05:10.226
[laughs]

05:10.310 --> 05:11.561
- Hey. Hey.

05:11.644 --> 05:13.146
Did you forget the secret code?

05:13.229 --> 05:16.524
- What secret code?

05:16.607 --> 05:19.277
Oh, oh, she's biting my ear!

05:19.360 --> 05:21.487
LOGAN: She's biting my ear.
She's biting my ear.

05:21.571 --> 05:24.407
Oh, oh, she's biting my ear.

05:24.490 --> 05:28.786
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:28.870 --> 05:31.664
- I hate seeing you this upset.

05:31.748 --> 05:34.584
- I'm not upset, I'm happy.

05:34.667 --> 05:36.127
- Why?

05:36.210 --> 05:39.547
- Because Lola
made Logan's earlobe bleed.

05:39.630 --> 05:41.466
I enjoyed that.

05:41.549 --> 05:45.344
- Are you sure
you're not upset?

05:45.428 --> 05:47.430
- No.

05:47.513 --> 05:48.806
I'm embarrassed.

05:48.890 --> 05:50.683
- Well, don't be.
- Come on.

05:50.767 --> 05:52.602
Do you know what it's like

05:52.685 --> 05:55.480
being a 16-year-old guy
who's afraid of roller coasters?

05:55.563 --> 05:57.023
- Michael.

05:57.106 --> 05:58.357
- What?

05:58.441 --> 06:00.943
- Everyone has silly things
they're scared of.

06:01.027 --> 06:03.780
- Okay.
What are you scared of?

06:03.863 --> 06:05.364
- I'd be scared
if I were tied up

06:05.448 --> 06:07.575
and thrown into a cage
with hungry tigers.

06:07.658 --> 06:08.951
- Well, that makes sense.

06:09.035 --> 06:10.328
You're scared of hungry tigers.

06:10.411 --> 06:11.954
And I'm scared
of an amusement park ride

06:12.038 --> 06:15.917
that makes little children
go "whee!"

06:16.000 --> 06:18.419
<i>MAN:</i>
<i>♪ So you're made of diamond ♪</i>

06:18.503 --> 06:20.797
<i>♪ I'm made of glass ♪</i>

06:22.507 --> 06:25.593
[students snickering]

06:42.318 --> 06:45.279
BOY: Look, there he is.
That's Michael.

06:50.368 --> 06:53.746
He's scared of roller coasters.

06:53.830 --> 06:56.332
- Hey, Michael,
what you drinking?

06:56.415 --> 06:58.835
- Blix.
- Wow, pretty brave.

06:58.918 --> 07:00.294
- What do you mean?

07:00.378 --> 07:02.338
- You know, fruity drinks
can be scary.

07:02.421 --> 07:05.466
[both laughing]

07:12.431 --> 07:14.350
- Hey, can I get next game?

07:14.433 --> 07:15.434
- You're gonna play pool?

07:15.518 --> 07:17.687
- Yeah, so?
- Pool?

07:17.770 --> 07:20.022
Big sticks, balls moving around?

07:20.106 --> 07:23.067
Thought that might be
a little too scary for you.

07:23.151 --> 07:26.195
[both laughing]

07:29.574 --> 07:31.492
- Hey, Michael, here.

07:31.576 --> 07:32.743
- What's this?

07:32.827 --> 07:33.786
- A teddy bear night light

07:33.870 --> 07:36.539
in case you get scared
of the dark.

07:36.622 --> 07:39.709
[both laughing]

07:39.792 --> 07:41.669
BOTH: Whoa.

07:50.595 --> 07:52.889
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:52.972 --> 07:56.475
- No, I swear, roller coasters.

07:56.559 --> 07:58.561
I know, he's 16 years old

07:58.644 --> 07:59.604
and the dude's afraid
of roller--

07:59.687 --> 08:01.063
Ah!
<i>WOMAN: Logan.</i>

08:01.147 --> 08:02.106
- You told everybody

08:02.190 --> 08:03.941
that I'm afraid
of roller coasters.

08:04.025 --> 08:06.402
- James, I think
he's about to kill me.

08:06.485 --> 08:08.029
Little help.
- Hang on.

08:08.112 --> 08:09.822
I'm organizing this playlist.

08:09.906 --> 08:13.868
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

08:16.329 --> 08:19.832
- Hey, you think a duck
would make a good pet?

08:19.916 --> 08:21.918
- A duck?
- Yeah.

08:22.001 --> 08:23.753
- I doubt it.

08:23.836 --> 08:25.755
- Yeah, me too.

08:25.838 --> 08:28.090
[cell phone ringing]

08:28.174 --> 08:29.675
- Hello?

08:29.759 --> 08:32.345
Firewire?

08:32.428 --> 08:35.597
How did you get my number?

08:35.681 --> 08:37.099
What?
- What?

08:37.183 --> 08:38.558
- Michael's torturing Logan.

08:38.643 --> 08:40.770
We'll be right there.

08:40.852 --> 08:43.522
No, I won't go out with you.

08:43.606 --> 08:44.524
Come on.

08:44.607 --> 08:46.275
- Okay!

08:46.359 --> 08:47.568
Wait.

08:47.652 --> 08:50.613
What if you could train a duck
to use a litter box?

08:50.696 --> 08:51.906
- [scoffs]

08:56.869 --> 08:58.371
LOGAN: Ah. Quit it. Let me go.

08:58.454 --> 08:59.789
- Whoa--
- Holy--

08:59.872 --> 09:02.583
- Go away, I'm busy.

09:02.667 --> 09:04.543
- Ow. Help me.

09:04.627 --> 09:05.711
- Why are you doing this?

09:05.795 --> 09:07.296
- 'Cause that nub
told half of PCA

09:07.380 --> 09:09.924
that I'm afraid
of roller coasters.

09:10.007 --> 09:11.300
- Why'd you have to do that?

09:11.384 --> 09:12.843
- The people
have a right to know.

09:14.887 --> 09:16.639
That one went in my mouth.

09:16.722 --> 09:18.599
- Okay, this is insane.

09:18.683 --> 09:20.810
James, why aren't you
doing anything?

09:20.893 --> 09:22.144
- I am.

09:22.228 --> 09:23.646
I'm making you
a really cool playlist.

09:23.729 --> 09:24.939
- Aww.

09:25.022 --> 09:27.191
- Can I?
- Please.

09:28.192 --> 09:29.151
- Oww.

09:29.235 --> 09:30.653
- Lola.

09:30.736 --> 09:32.488
- He deserves it
for making me a laughingstock

09:32.572 --> 09:33.781
in my own school.

09:33.864 --> 09:35.449
- But this isn't the way
to handle it.

09:35.533 --> 09:36.909
- I think I'm starting
to lose consciousness.

09:36.993 --> 09:39.620
- If you're so worried
about people finding out

09:39.704 --> 09:41.455
that you're afraid
of roller coasters,

09:41.539 --> 09:43.499
then get unafraid,
get over it.

09:43.582 --> 09:45.793
- How?
- You have to face your fear.

09:48.254 --> 09:50.631
- You know she's right.

09:50.715 --> 09:53.551
- Ow.

09:53.634 --> 09:55.219
- Let him down.

09:55.303 --> 09:56.762
- Okay.

10:01.600 --> 10:03.060
- Ow.

10:06.689 --> 10:14.697
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:23.039 --> 10:24.373
MICHAEL: I don't like this.

10:24.457 --> 10:25.625
I don't like this one bit.

10:25.708 --> 10:27.043
- You're perfectly safe.

10:27.126 --> 10:29.462
- It's just a Hickenbackker
G-force turbo chair.

10:29.545 --> 10:30.671
- Yeah, just your everyday

10:30.755 --> 10:32.214
Hickenbackker
G-force turbo chair.

10:32.298 --> 10:34.300
- It's used to help
astronauts and fighter pilots

10:34.383 --> 10:35.676
experience the feelings

10:35.760 --> 10:37.345
of high-speed vertical
and lateral movements.

10:37.428 --> 10:39.889
- Look, I just wanna go
back to my dorm, lie down,

10:39.972 --> 10:41.349
and experience my head
on my pillow.

10:41.432 --> 10:43.100
- You should be happy
about this.

10:43.184 --> 10:44.352
- It's gonna cure your fear.

10:44.435 --> 10:46.020
- Without going
on a real roller coaster.

10:46.103 --> 10:47.063
- You might even have fun.

10:47.146 --> 10:48.397
- If it's gonna be fun,

10:48.481 --> 10:50.983
then why did Lola lock my wrist
down to the chair?

10:51.067 --> 10:53.819
- Do you think a duck
would make a good pet?

10:53.903 --> 10:56.155
- A duck?
What do ducks have to do with--

10:56.238 --> 10:57.615
- Okay, Michael,
you just relax,

10:57.698 --> 11:00.242
while I create the effects
for real roller coaster.

11:00.326 --> 11:02.912
Lola, blindfold him.

11:02.995 --> 11:04.830
- Why do I have
to be blindfolded?

11:04.914 --> 11:06.207
- It helps you
block out reality

11:06.290 --> 11:07.666
and focus on the feelings.

11:11.337 --> 11:12.546
- Michael, look out.

11:12.630 --> 11:14.256
- What? What?
- Kidding.

11:14.340 --> 11:18.302
- Okay, we'll start
with some basic easy movements.

11:21.347 --> 11:22.264
- See, you're fine, right?

11:22.348 --> 11:25.518
- Yeah, yeah, I guess.

11:25.601 --> 11:27.978
- Okay, now,
as the speed and intensity

11:28.062 --> 11:30.439
of the roller coaster increases,
you'll hear the sounds

11:30.523 --> 11:32.108
and feel the wind on your face.

11:32.191 --> 11:34.735
- I hate speed and intensity.

11:43.452 --> 11:44.829
- You're doing great.

11:44.912 --> 11:46.205
- Okay.

11:46.288 --> 11:49.500
Now the roller coaster's
gonna get a little more intense.

11:49.583 --> 11:52.002
- Why must it get more intense?

11:55.214 --> 11:56.632
- Hang in there, buddy.

11:56.715 --> 11:59.343
- [muttering]

11:59.427 --> 12:00.803
QUINN: Okay.

12:00.886 --> 12:03.180
Now imagine you're climbing.

12:04.390 --> 12:05.683
Climbing.

12:05.766 --> 12:09.061
Almost at the top of the hill...

12:11.147 --> 12:14.442
QUINN: And...

12:14.525 --> 12:15.651
wheeee.

12:15.734 --> 12:17.486
ALL: Wheeee.

12:17.570 --> 12:19.947
<i>[screams]</i>

12:20.030 --> 12:21.532
- Ahh!

12:21.615 --> 12:24.034
I hate it! I hate it!
I hate it! I hate it!

12:24.118 --> 12:25.703
Pull the plug! Pull the plug!

12:25.786 --> 12:27.121
- Turn it off!

12:27.204 --> 12:29.665
MICHAEL: Pull the plug.
Pull the plug.

12:29.748 --> 12:31.542
Pull the plug. Pull the plug.

12:31.625 --> 12:33.210
[sobbing]

12:33.294 --> 12:36.213
[screaming]

12:36.297 --> 12:38.090
- Michael!
- Stop!

12:38.174 --> 12:40.509
- He'll stop.
- Yeah, there's a fence.

12:40.593 --> 12:42.553
- No!

12:42.636 --> 12:44.013
Ow.

12:50.728 --> 12:52.271
<i>MAN: ♪ Here we go ♪</i>

12:52.354 --> 12:53.105
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

12:53.189 --> 12:55.733
<i>♪ But I can't fall ♪</i>

12:55.816 --> 12:58.402
- In 1616, Sir Walter Raleigh
was released

12:58.486 --> 12:59.528
from the Tower of London

12:59.612 --> 13:01.363
in order to conduct
a second expedition

13:01.447 --> 13:02.698
to the what river?

13:02.781 --> 13:03.866
- Here's my feeling
on the whole

13:03.949 --> 13:05.201
roller coaster situation.

13:05.284 --> 13:06.243
- Okay.

13:06.327 --> 13:08.787
- So I'm afraid
of roller coasters.

13:08.871 --> 13:09.997
So?
- Yeah, so?

13:10.080 --> 13:12.917
- Doesn't make me a bad person.
- Of course not.

13:13.000 --> 13:15.211
- It's not like
I'm a street thug or bank robber

13:15.294 --> 13:17.505
or person who downloads music
illegally, right?

13:17.588 --> 13:19.048
- Honestly, I never cared

13:19.131 --> 13:21.133
if you were afraid
of roller coasters or not.

13:21.217 --> 13:22.635
- Swear?

13:22.718 --> 13:24.386
- Swear.
- Well, see?

13:24.470 --> 13:25.429
That's all that matters.

13:25.513 --> 13:27.306
I don't care
what other people think.

13:27.389 --> 13:28.891
If you will still love me
and my grandma still loves me,

13:28.974 --> 13:32.228
and I'm still attractive--
- [screams]

13:32.311 --> 13:35.564
- What? What?

13:35.648 --> 13:37.691
- [screaming]

13:37.775 --> 13:39.068
Millie. Millie.

13:39.151 --> 13:40.402
Millie, come here, come here.

13:40.486 --> 13:41.362
- What's wrong?
- There's a spider right there.

13:41.445 --> 13:43.239
Look, see it?

13:47.618 --> 13:50.412
- There. All dead.

13:50.496 --> 13:51.664
- Thanks.
- Sure.

13:51.747 --> 13:52.790
See you in yoga tomorrow.

13:52.873 --> 13:54.875
- Okay. Bye.

13:56.335 --> 13:58.420
What?

13:58.504 --> 13:59.797
- Why didn't you ask me
to get the spider?

13:59.880 --> 14:00.923
